Vehicles are great for covering long distances on the map in a short time, perfect for out running the gas or if you have a kill bounty on your team it’s great for getting away quickly. But they paint you bright red on the mini map for all to see. That’s why generally I avoid them and when running to the next circle I move cover to cover just in front of the gas so to avoid being killed by another team behind me. Most people try to keep way ahead of the gas but if you move with it as it closes, your back is protected. But yes I do agree vehicles aren’t overpowered at all, it’s very rare for someone to become road kill and let’s face it, how often do you see a helo or armored truck in the final circle? I’m not great at Warzone and I suck with vehicles but I don’t complain about it
